title: 'Sturdy and minimalist design'
body: I recently purchased this wake fit work-from-home table, and I must say it has been a game-changer for my remote work setup. Its sturdy construction provides a reliable workspace, allowing me to be productive throughout the day. It’s having minimalistic design and offers good ground clearance.  The design is both sleek and functional, fitting seamlessly into my home decor. The ample surface area comfortably accommodates my laptop, monitor, keyboard, and other work essentials.  Overall, I highly recommend this work-from-home table to anyone looking to enhance their remote work experience. It's a great investment.

title: 'Conducive'
body: 'The media could not be loaded. Good fit for basic wfh set up has cabinets for bare minimum usage. Not that heavy material for keeping legs under the slab because it’s quite weak. Serves the purpose in case you’re on hybrid working mode.'

title: 'Great work desk as per the price range'
body: 'The desk is really good and efficient for Work from home setup or as a study table. It is sturdy and has enough leg space. This also gives you 1 year of warranty. This is all you need go for it with no hesitation. Happy with my experience.'

title: 'Sturdy and spacious table'
body: 'Table is really good and sturdy. Plenty of space in drawer and cabinet to store stuff. A cutout backside of the table would be a plus.'

title: 'WORST SERVICE AND TABLE'
body: 'Ordered study table from wakefit bad decision This is based on true events. On first delivery they delievered broken table On the second delievey they forget to send the carpenter to install the table After three days i decided to return the table and now they are saying it is not returnable. You should apparently change your name to worstfit'
